     2â†’/**
     3â†’ * WorkCompletionLearning.hook.ts - Extract Learnings from Completed Work (SessionEnd)
     4â†’ *
     5â†’ * PURPOSE:
     6â†’ * Bridges the WORK/ system to the LEARNING/ system. When a session ends with
     7â†’ * significant work completed, this hook captures the work metadata (files changed,
     8â†’ * tools used, ideal state criteria) and creates a learning file for future reference.
     9â†’ * This ensures insights compound over time rather than being lost.
    10â†’ *
    11â†’ * TRIGGER: SessionEnd
    12â†’ *
    13â†’ * INPUT:
    14â†’ * - stdin: Hook input JSON (session_id, transcript_path)
    15â†’ * - Files: MEMORY/STATE/current-work.json, MEMORY/WORK/<dir>/META.yaml
    16â†’ *
    17â†’ * OUTPUT:
    18â†’ * - stdout: None
    19â†’ * - stderr: Status messages
    20â†’ * - exit(0): Always (non-blocking)
    21â†’ *
    22â†’ * SIDE EFFECTS:
    23â†’ * - Creates: MEMORY/LEARNING/<category>/<YYYY-MM>/<datetime>_work_<slug>.md
    24â†’ * - Reads: Current work state and work directory metadata
    25â†’ *
    26â†’ * INTER-HOOK RELATIONSHIPS:
    27â†’ * - DEPENDS ON: AutoWorkCreation (expects WORK/ structure)
    28â†’ * - COORDINATES WITH: SessionSummary (both run at SessionEnd)
    29â†’ * - MUST RUN BEFORE: SessionSummary (captures before state is cleared)
    30â†’ * - MUST RUN AFTER: Stop handlers (captures completed work)
    31â†’ *
    32â†’ * SIGNIFICANT WORK CRITERIA:
    33â†’ * A learning is only captured if:
    34â†’ * - Files were changed, OR
    35â†’ * - Multiple items exist in work directory, OR
    36â†’ * - Work was manually created (source: MANUAL)
    37â†’ *
    38â†’ * LEARNING CATEGORIES:
    39â†’ * - ALGORITHM: Insights about process/approach improvement
    40â†’ * - SYSTEM: Technical system improvements
    41â†’ * (Determined by getLearningCategory utility)
    42â†’ *
    43â†’ * ERROR HANDLING:
    44â†’ * - No active work: Silent exit
    45â†’ * - Missing META.yaml: Silent exit
    46â†’ * - Write failures: Logged to stderr, silent exit
    47â†’ *
    48â†’ * PERFORMANCE:
    49â†’ * - Non-blocking: Yes (fire-and-forget at session end)
    50â†’ * - Typical execution: <100ms
    51â†’ */
