     2â†’/**
     3â†’ * SessionSummary.hook.ts - Mark Work Complete and Clear State (SessionEnd)
     4â†’ *
     5â†’ * PURPOSE:
     6â†’ * Finalizes a Claude Code session by marking the current work directory as
     7â†’ * COMPLETED and clearing the session state. This ensures clean session boundaries
     8â†’ * and accurate work tracking.
     9â†’ *
    10â†’ * TRIGGER: SessionEnd
    11â†’ *
    12â†’ * INPUT:
    13â†’ * - stdin: Hook input JSON (session_id, transcript_path)
    14â†’ * - Files: MEMORY/STATE/current-work.json
    15â†’ *
    16â†’ * OUTPUT:
    17â†’ * - stdout: None
    18â†’ * - stderr: Status messages
    19â†’ * - exit(0): Always (non-blocking)
    20â†’ *
    21â†’ * SIDE EFFECTS:
    22â†’ * - Updates: MEMORY/WORK/<dir>/META.yaml (status: COMPLETED, completed_at timestamp)
    23â†’ * - Deletes: MEMORY/STATE/current-work.json (clears session state)
    24â†’ *
    25â†’ * INTER-HOOK RELATIONSHIPS:
    26â†’ * - DEPENDS ON: AutoWorkCreation (expects WORK/ structure and current-work.json)
    27â†’ * - COORDINATES WITH: WorkCompletionLearning (both run at SessionEnd)
    28â†’ * - MUST RUN BEFORE: None (final cleanup)
    29â†’ * - MUST RUN AFTER: WorkCompletionLearning (learning capture uses state before clear)
    30â†’ *
    31â†’ * STATE TRANSITIONS:
    32â†’ * - META.yaml status: "ACTIVE" â†’ "COMPLETED"
    33â†’ * - META.yaml completed_at: null â†’ ISO timestamp
    34â†’ * - current-work.json: exists â†’ deleted
    35â†’ *
    36â†’ * DESIGN NOTES:
    37â†’ * - Does NOT write to SESSIONS/ directory (WORK/ is the primary tracking system)
    38â†’ * - Deleting current-work.json signals a clean slate for next session
    39â†’ *
    40â†’ * ERROR HANDLING:
    41â†’ * - No current work: Logs message, exits gracefully
    42â†’ * - Missing META.yaml: Skips update, continues to state clear
    43â†’ * - File operation failures: Logged to stderr
    44â†’ *
    45â†’ * PERFORMANCE:
    46â†’ * - Non-blocking: Yes
    47â†’ * - Typical execution: <50ms
    48â†’ */
